<h2 id="connections-to-trump">Connections to Trump</h2>
<p>JMI is listed as an advisory board member of Project 2025, an initiative by the Heritage Foundation aimed at shaping conservative policy for future Republican administrations. This connection highlights JMIâ€™s alignment with broader conservative agendas, including those supported by Trump and his affiliates.</p>

<h2 id="concerns">Concerns</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Political Bias:</strong> JMIâ€™s strong advocacy for free-market principles and limited government may lead to concerns about potential biases in its research and policy recommendations. The organizationâ€™s alignment with conservative agendas could influence its objectivity.</li>
  <li><strong>Influence on Policy:</strong> JMIâ€™s significant role in shaping state policy, particularly in Florida, underscores the importance of scrutinizing its recommendations to ensure they serve the public interest.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
<p>The James Madison Institute is a key player in promoting conservative values and free-market principles in Florida and across the United States. Its research and advocacy efforts have a considerable impact on public policy, particularly in areas such as economic freedom, education, and regulatory reform. However, its strong ideological stance and connections to conservative movements warrant careful consideration of its policy recommendations and research outputs.</p>

